<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<section xml:id="sec-set_descrp" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Description</title>

  <p> 
    Sets are represented by three different forms: 
    <ol>
      <li>
       <p>
        Description or Statement Form: <me> 2, 4, 6, 8, \ldots = \{\text{even numbers} \}</me> by using statement.
        <me> a, e, i, o, u = \{\text{vowels of english alphabet} \}</me>
       </p>
       </li>
      <li>
      <p>
        Roster or Tabular Form: <me>\{ a, \, e,\, i,\,o, \,u \}</me> by using commas.
      </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          Set-Builder or Rule Form: <me>\{ x: x \text{ is a vowel} \}</me> 
          or  
          <me>\{ x| x \text{ is a vowel} \}</me>  
          by using its property.
        </p>
      </li>
    </ol> 
  </p>
  <p>
    See examples in <xref ref="sec_set-exampleA"/>.
  </p>




</section>